<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-07-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Perry</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United States Consulate</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Tunis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-07-04"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 4, 1863</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to report that a loan
                            spoken of in a former despatch was made to the Tunisian government by
                            the bankers, (Messrs. Erlanger &amp; Co.,) favored by the French consul
                            general.</p>
                        <p>There has been recently much discussion about Tunisian affairs in English
                            and French journals, in dictating an imbittered state of feeling, and
                            that England and Turkey are opposed to French influence in this
                            place.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, with great respect, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>AMOS PERRY.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>